The '''Food Hygiene Rating (Wales) Act 2013''' ''anaw 2''<ref>{{cite web|last=Legislation.gov.uk|title=Food Hygiene Ratings (Wales) Act 2013|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/anaw/2013/2/contents/enacted|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=31 March 2014}}</ref> is an [[Act of the National Assembly for Wales]] to make [[food hygiene]] ratings mandatory. The ratings are also to be made public through use of a Food Hygiene Sticker.<ref>{{cite web|last=Legislation.gov.uk|title=Food Hygiene Ratings (Wales) Act 2013 Section 3|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/anaw/2013/2/section/3/enacted|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=31 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Legislation.gov.uk|title=Food Hygiene Ratings (Wales) Act 2013 - Informing the public about food hygiene ratings|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/anaw/2013/2/crossheading/informing-the-public-about-food-hygiene-ratings/enacted|publisher=National Archives|accessdate=31 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jones|first=Martin|title=Mandatory food hygiene rating displays to be introduced in Wales in November 2013|url=http://www.hughjames.com/blogs/blog_library/2013/august/mandatory_food_hygiene_rating.aspx#.UzrtvPldWSo|publisher=Hugh James Solicitor|accessdate=1 April 2014}}</ref> Food Hygiene Ratings are available on the [[Food Standards Agency]] website.<ref>{{cite web|last=Food Standards Agency| title=Food hygiene ratings.|url=http://ratings.food.gov.uk}}</ref>
