'''Honeymoon rhinitis''' is a condition in which the sufferer experiences [[nasal congestion]] during sexual intercourse.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Monteseirin | first1 = J. | last2 = Camacho | first2 = M. J. | last3 = Bonilla | first3 = I. | last4 = Sánchez-Hernández | first4 = C. | last5 = Hernández | first5 = M. | last6 = Conde | first6 = J. | doi = 10.1034/j.1398-9995.2001.00054.x | title = Honeymoon rhinitis | journal = Allergy | volume = 56 | issue = 4 | pages = 353–354 | date = Apr 2001| issn = 0105-4538| pmid = 11284809| pmc = }}</ref>
The condition appears to be genetically determined, and caused by the presence in the nose of erectile tissue which may become engorged during sexual arousal as a side effect of the signals from the [[autonomic nervous system]] that trigger changes in the genitals of both men and women.
A related condition called [[sexually induced sneezing]] also exists, where people sneeze, sometimes uncontrollably, when engaging in or even thinking about sexual activity.<ref>{{cite news |date=19 December 2008 |title=Sneezing 'can be sign of arousal' |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/7792102.stm |publisher=[[BBC News]] |accessdate=26 May 2009}}</ref>
A phenomenon presumably related to 'honeymoon rhinitis' is the occurrence of nasal congestion as a reported side effect of [[Sildenafil|Viagra]] use.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Khan | first1 = L. A. | last2 = Khan | first2 = S. A. | last3 = Al-Hateeti | first3 = H. | title = Sildenafil (Viagra) may cause nasal stuffiness | journal = Annals of Saudi Medicine | volume = 19 | issue = 5 | pages = 468 | date = Sep 1999 | pmid = 17277525 | issn = 0256-4947}}</ref>
